♪<i> Gigolo...</i> ♪

01:18.179 --> 01:19.745
Showtime.

01:20.948 --> 01:22.848
♪<i> Ooh, and they're sayin'</i> ♪

01:22.850 --> 01:24.016
♪<i> Gigolo, gigolo, gigolo...</i> ♪

01:24.018 --> 01:25.517
Your tea, Nana.

01:25.519 --> 01:28.020
(laughs)
Sweet darling boy.

01:28.022 --> 01:29.388
BART:<i> I know</i>
<i> what you're thinking.</i>

01:29.390 --> 01:31.223
<i> This must be</i>
<i> some kind of prank.</i>

01:31.225 --> 01:33.725
<i> Is there laxative</i>
<i> in the punch bowl?</i>

01:33.727 --> 01:36.395
<i> Well, there is, but</i>
<i> their doctors prescribed that.</i>

01:36.397 --> 01:37.563
<i> I've changed.</i>

01:37.565 --> 01:38.797
<i> I've become pinchable.</i>

01:38.799 --> 01:40.399
<i> You look confused.</i>

01:40.401 --> 01:43.235
<i> Why don't I start</i>
<i> from the beginning?</i>

01:43.237 --> 01:45.904
♪<i> Grandpa, Grandma</i> ♪

01:45.906 --> 01:47.406
♪<i> We love you</i> ♪

01:47.408 --> 01:50.375
♪<i> We will show</i>
<i> what school can do</i> ♪

01:50.377 --> 01:53.245
♪<i> We cleaned our desk,</i>
<i> we learned this song</i> ♪

01:53.247 --> 01:56.381
♪<i> Teachers beat us</i>
<i> when you're gone</i> ♪

01:56.383 --> 01:59.718
♪<i> Grandma, grandpa,</i>
<i> you're the best</i> ♪

01:59.720 --> 02:02.254
♪<i> Now you can be laid to rest.</i> ♪

02:02.256 --> 02:05.224
Simpson. Those lyrics are
unapproved and not that funny.

02:05.226 --> 02:06.325
Come with me.

02:06.327 --> 02:07.926
Hey, Skinner.

02:07.928 --> 02:10.562
Sure, you're tough enough
to punish a little boy,

02:10.564 --> 02:13.432
but what about a
Marine Corps veteran?

02:13.434 --> 02:15.767
Oh.

02:15.769 --> 02:17.636
Mm-hmm.

02:17.638 --> 02:18.937
Okay, Seymour.

02:18.939 --> 02:20.572
Note to my mom or detention?

02:20.574 --> 02:24.343
Which of your two lame weapons
are you gonna unleash on me?

02:24.345 --> 02:25.944
I have other weapons.

02:25.946 --> 02:27.779
SKINNER:
<i> I have no other weapons.</i>

02:27.781 --> 02:30.249
Seymour, walk me
to the bus stop.

02:30.251 --> 02:31.683
Mother, what are you doing here?

02:31.685 --> 02:33.418
I wanted to make sure
you remember

02:33.420 --> 02:35.687
that I think your job is stupid.

02:40.928 --> 02:43.295
Simpson, I thought
of your punishment.

02:43.297 --> 02:45.430
Bart here will walk you
to the bus stop.

02:45.432 --> 02:47.266
That'll kill two birds
with one stone.

02:47.268 --> 02:48.467
(chuckles)

02:48.469 --> 02:51.103
First time a worm
ever killed a bird.

02:51.105 --> 02:52.971
(Bart laughs)

02:52.973 --> 02:54.973
LENNY:
<i> Okay, Lenny, don't be nervous.</i>

02:54.975 --> 02:57.876
This is the big one.

03:00.147 --> 03:01.813
Gotcha! Where am I?

03:01.815 --> 03:04.049
(scoffs)
You walked in the core.

03:04.051 --> 03:06.218
Yeah, we better seal
this thing up tight.

03:10.291 --> 03:11.823
(meows)

03:11.825 --> 03:14.393
I'm playing<i> Peekimon Get,</i> see?

03:14.395 --> 03:17.162
That's a wild Rotata.

03:17.164 --> 03:20.465
That has got to be the stupidest
game I've ever heard of.

03:20.467 --> 03:22.334
Oh, yeah, you're right.
It's really a kids' game.

03:22.336 --> 03:23.569
And it's silly for me to...

03:23.571 --> 03:26.538
Quiet, I'm playing it.

03:26.540 --> 03:27.739
(air horn blows)

03:27.741 --> 03:29.174
Quitting time.

03:29.176 --> 03:31.043
Three-day weekend.

03:33.247 --> 03:35.013
(Homer yelping in panic)

03:35.015 --> 03:37.015
Haw-haw!

03:37.017 --> 03:38.417
♪<i> Bart's holding hands</i> ♪

03:38.419 --> 03:40.485
♪<i> With an old lady</i> ♪

03:40.487 --> 03:42.754
♪<i> Who seems kind of sweet</i> ♪

03:42.756 --> 03:45.023
♪<i> And my grandmas are gone</i> ♪

03:45.025 --> 03:49.027
♪<i> One's in jail,</i>
<i> and one's in dirt jail.</i> ♪

03:49.029 --> 03:50.996
Back in a flash, Grandmama.

03:50.998 --> 03:54.600
Try not to win any beauty
pageants while I'm gone.

03:54.602 --> 03:57.202
Oh.
(laughs)

03:57.204 --> 03:59.204
Agnes!

03:59.206 --> 04:02.274
Oh, you just missed my
perfect little Martin.

04:02.276 --> 04:03.875
Eh, I saw him.

04:03.877 --> 04:06.011
He's beefing up,
that's for sure.

04:06.013 --> 04:08.513
Don't you love
Grandparents' Day?

04:08.515 --> 04:11.550
I get to meet all the little
boys Martin snitches on.

04:11.552 --> 04:12.884
Is that your grandson?

04:12.886 --> 04:15.053
Or is this just
a... a pity walk?

04:15.055 --> 04:17.055
He's not...
A pity walker?

04:17.057 --> 04:18.957
I love my Gam-Gam.

04:18.959 --> 04:21.059
Ha. You hear that?

04:21.061 --> 04:22.127
Gam-Gam.

04:22.129 --> 04:23.395
What's your pet name?

04:23.397 --> 04:24.563
Gram-Gram.

04:24.565 --> 04:25.564
That's the stupidest thing

04:25.566 --> 04:26.965
I've ever heard.

04:26.967 --> 04:29.801
I can't believe
Martin left you alone

04:29.803 --> 04:32.237
in this cold hallway.

04:32.239 --> 04:33.472
Thanks, Peaches.

04:33.474 --> 04:34.973
You're a gift to this world.

04:34.975 --> 04:37.876
You deserve
to be wrapped up, Gam-Gam.

04:37.878 --> 04:39.077
Gam-Gam-Gam.
(laughs)

04:39.079 --> 04:40.412
Gam-Gam-Gam.

04:40.414 --> 04:42.247
For you, Grandmama.

04:42.249 --> 04:46.251
A diorama of the sky
from the night you were born.

04:46.253 --> 04:47.586
Give me
your sweater.

04:47.588 --> 04:50.255
But-but without it,
I'm nippley.

04:50.257 --> 04:51.657
(both laugh)

04:51.659 --> 04:55.260
You hear that? Oh, no...

04:55.262 --> 04:56.728
BART:
Nippley.

04:58.065 --> 05:01.166
I always wanted a grandson.

05:01.168 --> 05:04.936
A cute little guy I could take
to the circus and the movies.

05:04.938 --> 05:07.606
Someone I could spoil rotten.

05:07.608 --> 05:09.441
I'm halfway there, ma'am.

05:09.443 --> 05:11.610
Well, this is my bus.

05:11.612 --> 05:15.113
Goes right by the
candy store, eh?

05:15.115 --> 05:18.917
Don't take my mother, I need her
to make me French toast!

05:18.919 --> 05:20.986
Egg yolks scare me...

05:28.529 --> 05:30.529
Ooh, a Rattlesnitch.

05:30.531 --> 05:31.930
(rattling)

05:31.932 --> 05:35.133
(laughing, whooping)

05:35.135 --> 05:37.469
Got it.

05:37.471 --> 05:38.970
Got it.
<i> Lo tango.</i>

05:38.972 --> 05:40.806
Duffman has got it.

05:40.808 --> 05:42.040
Got it.

05:42.042 --> 05:43.809
Got it.
Got it.

05:43.811 --> 05:44.943
Got it.

05:44.945 --> 05:46.144
Got it.

05:46.146 --> 05:47.646
Got it.
Got it.

05:47.648 --> 05:49.614
Now that's a spicy Peekiball.

05:49.616 --> 05:50.649
Got it.

05:50.651 --> 05:51.983
(gibbering)

05:51.985 --> 05:54.619
And so...
Aw, I didn't get it.

05:54.621 --> 05:57.656
Won't anyone help me?

05:57.658 --> 06:00.192
Got it, and no.

06:01.495 --> 06:04.730
Now Maggie, there's no
monster under your bed.

06:04.732 --> 06:06.631
Ooh, there is one on your face.

06:08.135 --> 06:11.403
Oh, man, there's like
a million in here.

06:11.405 --> 06:13.138
Here's the phone,
so you can see them.

06:13.140 --> 06:14.206
Nighty night.

06:16.343 --> 06:19.010
<i> (creatures growling)</i>

06:19.012 --> 06:21.246
In the gospel
according to Luke, uh...

06:21.248 --> 06:24.082
(sighs)
If you two don't mind.

06:24.084 --> 06:26.818
Look this game is,
or at least was,

06:26.820 --> 06:28.854
bigger than Jesus, okay?

06:28.856 --> 06:31.656
Hmm, that's a pretty low bar
these days.

06:33.026 --> 06:35.527
Ah, Skunk-a-san.

06:35.529 --> 06:38.597
Why can't I capture you?

06:38.599 --> 06:40.198
(screams)
It's real!

06:40.200 --> 06:41.366
D'oh!

06:41.368 --> 06:43.702
(gargling)

06:43.704 --> 06:45.837
(moaning)

06:45.839 --> 06:48.039
Sprayed by a skunk.

06:48.041 --> 06:50.709
Homie, that game's
too dangerous.

06:50.711 --> 06:52.110
The game was fine.

06:52.112 --> 06:53.712
Reality was dangerous.

06:53.714 --> 06:55.180
And could you move
a little to your left?

06:55.182 --> 06:56.882
There's a Stumble-Bee
right behind you.

06:56.884 --> 06:59.885
Oh, is there any fad
you don't take too far?

06:59.887 --> 07:01.286
The aerobics ones.

07:01.288 --> 07:03.789
Mom, what Dad could
use is a co-player,

07:03.791 --> 07:05.757
who makes sure he
doesn't get hurt.

07:05.759 --> 07:07.459
Because the game
<i> is</i> good for him.

07:07.461 --> 07:10.228
You can see that he's lost
weight from the walking.

07:10.230 --> 07:12.697
I'm using the factory holes
on my belt.

07:12.699 --> 07:14.866
Oh, wow. Wow.

07:14.868 --> 07:16.935
Lisa, why are you interested?

07:16.937 --> 07:19.404
Because it's the
greatest game ever.

07:19.406 --> 07:22.307
In this world, I
can throw a ball.

07:22.309 --> 07:24.042
Hmm, okay.

07:24.044 --> 07:25.577
(grunts)

07:25.579 --> 07:28.079
I'd prefer if you didn't
turn your skunk bath

07:28.081 --> 07:29.981
into a giant cocktail.

07:29.983 --> 07:34.152
Ugh. One damn rule after
another around here.

07:35.155 --> 07:37.456
Peekisaurus at the Kwik-E-Mart.

07:38.926 --> 07:40.325
Please come in.

07:40.327 --> 07:42.761
Enjoy your game
from which I do not make a dime.

07:42.763 --> 07:44.763
(laughs) I'll be darned
if this little critter

07:44.765 --> 07:46.598
doesn't look like your god.

07:46.600 --> 07:48.500
And I'll be darned
if this sad wino

07:48.502 --> 07:50.268
doesn't look like your god.

07:50.270 --> 07:54.072
Do unto Snickers as you would
have Snickers do unto you.

07:54.074 --> 07:55.340
♪ ♪

07:57.010 --> 07:58.276
Oh.

07:58.278 --> 07:59.945
Well.

07:59.947 --> 08:02.781
Such good manners.

08:02.783 --> 08:04.616
I went out to get you
some sneakers.

08:04.618 --> 08:07.118
The kind that gang members wear.

08:07.120 --> 08:09.120
BART:<i> Heaven.</i>
<i> But I couldn't help thinking,</i>

08:09.122 --> 08:10.956
<i> why settle</i>
<i> for one golden goose,</i>

08:10.958 --> 08:12.791
<i> when you can have a gaggle?</i>

08:12.793 --> 08:16.761
Bessie, have I seen
your grandkids in church?

08:16.763 --> 08:19.297
No. I don't have
any grandchildren.

08:19.299 --> 08:20.999
Here's my headshot.

08:21.001 --> 08:22.767
BESSIE:
Oh...

08:22.769 --> 08:25.303
BART: In fights with your
children, I take your side.

08:25.305 --> 08:26.538
(gasps) And
what's this?

08:28.475 --> 08:30.809
I have a loose tooth.

08:30.811 --> 08:33.011
Oh!

08:33.013 --> 08:35.480
(Bart chuckles)

08:35.482 --> 08:37.782
♪ ♪

08:37.784 --> 08:39.618
BART:<i> It might've felt</i>
<i> more like a lie</i>

08:39.620 --> 08:41.653
<i> if I had to say</i>
<i> the word "grandmother."</i>

08:41.655 --> 08:45.557
<i> Fortunately, my ladies like</i>
<i> to be called anything but.</i>

08:46.860 --> 08:48.560
Good morning, Momo.

08:48.562 --> 08:50.228
I love you, Geema.

08:50.230 --> 08:51.563
Momtom!

08:51.565 --> 08:52.998
<i> Na-nee!</i>

08:53.000 --> 08:54.399
<i> Ugogo!</i>

08:54.401 --> 08:55.867
<i> Waipo.</i>

08:55.869 --> 08:58.803
Hey, who wants a box
full of firecrackers?

08:58.805 --> 09:01.139
They won't light up
the night like you.

09:01.141 --> 09:03.241
Aw.

09:03.243 --> 09:05.577
<i> Man, nothing beats</i>
<i> ladies in their 80s.</i>

09:05.579 --> 09:07.178
<i> Twice my age plus 60.</i>

09:07.180 --> 09:08.413
<i> Perfect.</i>

09:09.883 --> 09:12.717
♪ ♪

09:18.325 --> 09:20.992
(screaming)

09:25.198 --> 09:26.431
(whirring)

09:32.539 --> 09:34.339
(steam whistle blows)

09:34.341 --> 09:36.441
Ketchup? In my kitchen?

09:36.443 --> 09:38.009
Never!

09:38.011 --> 09:39.711
(laughs)

09:39.713 --> 09:41.446
(whistling)

09:42.683 --> 09:43.882
Bart?

09:43.884 --> 09:45.617
Hey, Mom. Want a
pep-o-mint drop?

09:45.619 --> 09:48.920
Yes, but since when
do you carry those?

09:48.922 --> 09:50.021
Oh, I got it all.

09:50.023 --> 09:51.957
Altoids, butterscotch candy,

09:51.959 --> 09:54.359
Jelly Bellies, and
Turkish delight.

09:54.361 --> 09:55.894
(phone ringing)

09:55.896 --> 09:57.395
Hello?

09:57.397 --> 09:58.897
It's someone named Gertie.

09:58.899 --> 10:00.799
Is that a girl in your class?

10:00.801 --> 10:02.534
I know a lot of Gerties.

10:02.536 --> 10:04.369
Did it sound like she was
talking through her throat?

10:04.371 --> 10:07.238
Uh, I'll just give you
the phone.

10:07.240 --> 10:09.407
GERTIE (through electrolarynx):
<i> Hello, sweetie, I didn't know</i>

10:09.409 --> 10:12.410
<i> if you wanted</i>
<i> PlayStation or Xbox,</i>

10:12.412 --> 10:15.113
<i> so I got both.</i>

10:17.618 --> 10:19.484
Maw-maw? I ordered
so many toys,

10:19.486 --> 10:20.752
you get
free shipping.

10:20.754 --> 10:22.053
Oh, so thoughtful.

10:23.256 --> 10:24.756
Interested?
My card.

10:24.758 --> 10:27.058
Book now for Christmas.

10:27.060 --> 10:30.061
<i> I was juggling</i>
<i> 50 shades of gray.</i>

10:30.063 --> 10:31.596
I've been
watching you.

10:31.598 --> 10:33.298
I know exactly
what you're up to.

10:33.300 --> 10:34.733
I'm not up to
anything, lady.

10:36.269 --> 10:38.169
(through electrolarynx):
This is for you.

10:38.171 --> 10:41.406
Thanks for coming to
my brother's wake.

10:41.408 --> 10:42.874
It's what I do.

10:49.816 --> 10:53.118
You are a cold little customer.

10:53.120 --> 10:54.853
Agreed. Now,
are we done here?

10:54.855 --> 10:57.188
Because I've got birthday
checks to deposit.

10:57.190 --> 10:59.624
I've got birthdays
like Lindy's has pickles.

10:59.626 --> 11:02.427
Do you even know what
that means? Do you?

11:02.429 --> 11:04.796
What is this? Pick On
the Con Artist Day?

11:04.798 --> 11:08.133
I'll pay you $100 to pick me up,
four days in a row,

11:08.135 --> 11:09.701
from the Sunnyday Nursing Home.

11:09.703 --> 11:11.870
Sunnyday,
that's on Fifth, right?

11:11.872 --> 11:14.372
Yes. Ask for Phoebe Pratt.

11:14.374 --> 11:17.442
Oh, my dear, you look
like Cybil Shepherd.

11:17.444 --> 11:19.144
I am Cybil Shepherd.

11:19.146 --> 11:22.013
Impossible, Cybil Shepherd
is notoriously difficult.

11:22.015 --> 11:23.515
Aah!

11:23.517 --> 11:25.750
Oh, my God, everyone,
it's Cybil Shepherd!

11:34.528 --> 11:37.028
So it turns out you
can buy Peeky creatures

11:37.030 --> 11:38.963
with real money.

11:38.965 --> 11:42.200
But the fun of the game is
catching them, not buying them.

11:42.202 --> 11:44.169
Lisa, I can think of
no better investment

11:44.171 --> 11:46.004
than invisible creatures
that are part of an over-hyped,

11:46.006 --> 11:47.305
passing fad.

11:47.307 --> 11:48.707
Please?
I'm in.

11:48.709 --> 11:52.010
You know, I'm really
starting to like you.

11:52.012 --> 11:53.611
Mmm.
Mmm.

11:54.915 --> 11:56.381
I'm here for Phoebe.

11:56.383 --> 11:58.583
Weren't you just
here for Eunice?

11:58.585 --> 12:00.351
Hey, a guy can have
two grandmothers.

12:00.353 --> 12:01.586
Look it up.

12:01.588 --> 12:03.822
All right, you've
served your purpose.

12:03.824 --> 12:05.190
Good-bye.

12:05.192 --> 12:07.025
A hundred bucks to
walk you to the curb?

12:07.027 --> 12:09.194
Sunnyday is a secure facility.

12:09.196 --> 12:12.030
A family member
must sign me out.

12:12.032 --> 12:14.699
Why are you there?
You seem normal.

12:14.701 --> 12:16.901
Happy anniversary.
Got it!

12:16.903 --> 12:19.871
My family fear I'll wander off
into some forest.

12:19.873 --> 12:21.372
So where are you going?

12:21.374 --> 12:22.741
Well, that forest over there.

12:22.743 --> 12:24.542
Mm, I better come with you.

12:24.544 --> 12:26.077
Those woods are full of bullies.

12:26.079 --> 12:27.746
So, did you get it?

12:27.748 --> 12:30.048
Yep, here's
the orzo.

12:30.050 --> 12:32.717
You idiot, you were
supposed to get ouzo.

12:32.719 --> 12:35.220
Orzo is, like,
thick, brown rice.

12:35.222 --> 12:36.688
You're like thick,
brown rice.

12:36.690 --> 12:38.089
(grunting)

12:42.529 --> 12:43.595
It's good stuff.

12:44.898 --> 12:47.098
So, Pheebs, tell me
about yourself.

12:47.100 --> 12:48.600
I'm a nature photographer.

12:48.602 --> 12:52.103
Wow, two things that
won't exist in 20 years.

12:58.044 --> 13:00.745
Oh, you're quite good at
taking the piss out of someone.

13:00.747 --> 13:02.313
Wait, that's
okay to say?

13:02.315 --> 13:03.948
Taking the piss.

13:03.950 --> 13:05.917
Taking the piss. Taking
the piss, taking the piss.

13:05.919 --> 13:07.619
♪<i> Taking the piss.</i> ♪

13:07.621 --> 13:09.554
Have you gotten that
out of your system?

13:09.556 --> 13:11.623
I'll get up in the middle
of the night and say one more.

13:12.726 --> 13:14.292
Poor old buck.

13:14.294 --> 13:17.428
Probably the last spring
he'll make it up the mountain.

13:17.430 --> 13:19.097
Want me to throw
a rock at it?

13:19.099 --> 13:20.598
No!

13:20.600 --> 13:23.101
He'll know
when his time has come.

13:23.103 --> 13:24.469
We all do.

13:25.472 --> 13:26.471
(bellows)

13:26.473 --> 13:28.807
Hey, I got to be me.

13:30.110 --> 13:31.776
Right, it's been four days.

13:31.778 --> 13:33.444
As we agreed.

13:33.446 --> 13:36.681
Um, I don't feel right
taking your money.

13:39.586 --> 13:41.352
I bequeath this to you.

13:41.354 --> 13:42.954
"Bequeath"?

13:42.956 --> 13:44.989
What does that mean?
Oh, look it up.

13:44.991 --> 13:46.491
Good-bye, Bart.

13:48.361 --> 13:49.694
<i> (snoring)</i>

13:49.696 --> 13:51.596
Aah!

13:51.598 --> 13:54.799
I'm having brunch with my little
man and I need the bus pass.

13:54.801 --> 13:56.634
Mother, you know that boy
is a ne'er-do-well

13:56.636 --> 13:58.503
and possibly a scofflaw.

13:58.505 --> 14:02.106
Seymour, it's time
you lived your life.

14:04.277 --> 14:05.944
I will live my life.

14:05.946 --> 14:08.813
And I'll start by leaving
my hair mussed up.

14:08.815 --> 14:10.315
MRS. SKINNER:
And comb that hair.

14:10.317 --> 14:13.184
I'll finger-comb it,
is what I'll do.

14:13.186 --> 14:14.519
BART:
<i> Oh, bequeath...</i>

14:14.521 --> 14:15.987
Bequeath, bequeath.

14:15.989 --> 14:17.655
I can't believe
she's making me do this.

14:17.657 --> 14:18.857
I'm gonna look up a word.

14:18.859 --> 14:20.592
How do you look up a word?

14:21.995 --> 14:23.628
I'd like to
look up a word.

14:23.630 --> 14:25.063
Give me your phone.

14:25.065 --> 14:26.798
What's the word?
"Bequeath."

14:28.835 --> 14:31.035
This means something
you give away when you die.

14:31.037 --> 14:32.337
She must be sick.

14:32.339 --> 14:33.638
How much do I owe you?

14:33.640 --> 14:35.173
Oh, no, it's...

14:35.175 --> 14:36.574
five dollars.

14:40.080 --> 14:42.847
I'm here to see Phoebe,
it's kind of a surprise.

14:42.849 --> 14:44.682
But she left this morning.

14:44.684 --> 14:46.150
She said you were
waiting outside

14:46.152 --> 14:47.719
and I didn't bother to check.

14:47.721 --> 14:50.154
What kind of a nursing home
are you running here?

14:50.156 --> 14:52.323
Oh, is it panic you want?

14:52.325 --> 14:55.026
Patient missing!
Patient missing!

14:55.028 --> 14:56.561
What's with
you, Judy?

14:56.563 --> 14:58.263
He knows my name.

15:02.702 --> 15:04.402
(alarm blaring)

15:04.404 --> 15:06.604
Those tracks were made
by tennis balls, Lou.

15:06.606 --> 15:08.606
Get me files on Pete Sampras

15:08.608 --> 15:10.608
and the Williams sisters.

15:10.610 --> 15:13.745
BART:<i> I realized she had me</i>
<i> pick her up four days in a row</i>

15:13.747 --> 15:15.580
<i> so the home's guard</i>
<i> would be down</i>

15:15.582 --> 15:17.115
<i>and she could leave on her own.</i>

15:17.117 --> 15:18.182
<i> But why?</i>

15:19.686 --> 15:21.886
He'll know
when his time has come.

15:21.888 --> 15:23.321
We all do.

15:24.257 --> 15:25.924
Can't believe I missed that.

15:25.926 --> 15:27.358
Or this.

15:27.360 --> 15:30.528
Don't tell anyone,
I plan to off myself.

15:30.530 --> 15:33.264
♪ ♪

15:33.266 --> 15:36.801
Okay, these Peekimon
cheats cost us 600 bucks.

15:36.803 --> 15:38.703
No one but you
or I must know.

15:40.874 --> 15:44.275
I'm starting to suspect that
trophy was not real gold.

15:44.277 --> 15:46.144
Can we talk about
something else?

15:46.146 --> 15:47.779
Absolutely.

15:47.781 --> 15:49.447
After you put your
fingerprints on this knife.

15:49.449 --> 15:50.715
Dad!

15:50.717 --> 15:51.983
It's a cake knife.

15:51.985 --> 15:53.484
I just had an extra piece.

15:53.486 --> 15:54.752
Two extra pieces.

15:54.754 --> 15:56.154
Okay, two extra cakes.

15:56.156 --> 15:57.822
But all cakes are pieces
of something bigger.

15:57.824 --> 15:59.424
Just touch the knife.

15:59.426 --> 16:02.727
Dad, why are you making me
hide things from Mom?

16:02.729 --> 16:03.728
You're right.

16:03.730 --> 16:04.963
That's my job.

16:04.965 --> 16:06.731
Well, it's my fault too.

16:06.733 --> 16:08.933
No, sweetie,
no more secrets.

16:08.935 --> 16:10.668
From now on
we're an open book.

16:10.670 --> 16:12.337
Guys!
How much did you hear?

16:12.339 --> 16:14.238
We may have to
get rid of the boy.

16:14.240 --> 16:15.773
I don't know what
you're talking about.

16:15.775 --> 16:18.443
I need you to look
for something.
Forget it.

16:18.445 --> 16:21.846
I learned from Peekimon
that's a slippery slope.

16:21.848 --> 16:24.682
Especially that time
I fell down a slippery slope.

16:24.684 --> 16:26.417
Look, this isn't
a stupid game.

16:26.419 --> 16:28.619
I'm looking for a lady
who may be in trouble.

16:28.621 --> 16:29.988
Is it Patty?
No.

16:29.990 --> 16:31.422
Is it Selma?
No!

16:31.424 --> 16:32.590
Let's roll.

16:33.927 --> 16:35.526
This is where we used to go.

16:35.528 --> 16:37.528
Bart, what were
you up to?

16:37.530 --> 16:39.097
Being the perfect grandson.

16:39.099 --> 16:40.465
For our grandma?

16:40.467 --> 16:42.033
No, for everybody but her.

16:42.035 --> 16:43.935
Now please,
we got to find Phoebe.

16:43.937 --> 16:46.671
Well, we'll need the help of...

16:46.673 --> 16:49.507
experienced Peekimon searchers.

16:49.509 --> 16:50.942
Hmm.

16:50.944 --> 16:52.643
This is who
we're looking for.

16:52.645 --> 16:54.479
Oh, you're no fun.

16:54.481 --> 16:56.381
What's her Peeki-name?

16:56.383 --> 16:58.716
Um... Dame Judi Dentures.

16:58.718 --> 17:00.018
(searchers laugh)

17:00.020 --> 17:01.652
And her point value?

17:01.654 --> 17:03.154
I don't know,
a zillion?

17:03.156 --> 17:04.889
(all exclaim)

17:04.891 --> 17:06.124
Okay, let's do it.

17:07.627 --> 17:09.360
♪ ♪

17:09.362 --> 17:12.330
LISA:
♪<i> I want to be the very best</i> ♪

17:12.332 --> 17:16.300
♪<i> This is my new career</i> ♪

17:16.302 --> 17:18.970
HOMER:
♪<i> And then take</i>
<i> a long, long rest</i> ♪

17:18.972 --> 17:22.673
♪<i> And celebrate with beer</i> ♪

17:22.675 --> 17:26.077
LISA:
♪<i> I will travel</i>
<i> across the land</i> ♪

17:26.079 --> 17:28.446
♪<i> Catching beasts</i>
<i> who've done no crime</i> ♪

17:29.816 --> 17:32.316
HOMER:
♪<i> Playing games made in Japan</i> ♪

17:32.318 --> 17:34.652
♪<i> I love to waste my time</i> ♪

17:36.022 --> 17:38.890
LISA:
♪<i> This is fun for everyone</i> ♪

17:38.892 --> 17:40.758
♪<i> Even babies play the game</i> ♪

17:42.328 --> 17:43.561
♪<i> Maggie cannot</i> ♪

17:43.563 --> 17:45.496
♪<i> Say a word</i> ♪

17:45.498 --> 17:48.132
♪<i> But watch her stab</i>
<i> and kill and maim.</i> ♪

17:51.271 --> 17:53.004
I found something.

17:53.006 --> 17:55.940
(owl hoots, bone crunches)

17:55.942 --> 17:57.408
Peekimon searchers, huh?

17:57.410 --> 17:58.943
Well, that's the stupidest thing
I've ever...

17:58.945 --> 18:00.211
Found her!

18:00.213 --> 18:01.512
(voice breaking):
Oh, my God.

18:06.386 --> 18:07.885
Hello.

18:07.887 --> 18:10.421
Oh, I-I seem to have
fallen asleep...

18:10.423 --> 18:11.722
in this forest...

18:11.724 --> 18:14.258
with apparently
excellent Wi-Fi.

18:14.260 --> 18:17.562
Uh, yes, all the trees
are cell phone towers.

18:17.564 --> 18:19.430
What are you
doing out here?

18:19.432 --> 18:22.800
Oh... I'll-I'll admit
I-I had some dark thoughts

18:22.802 --> 18:25.470
and I used you to
escape from the home.

18:25.472 --> 18:29.140
But once I got out here by
myself, completely free,

18:29.142 --> 18:31.976
I realized there's
so much to live for.

18:31.978 --> 18:34.412
And... I want my camera back.

18:34.414 --> 18:36.881
Can we still
hike sometimes?

18:36.883 --> 18:38.282
Yes, and we
could go inside

18:38.284 --> 18:40.118
that mill house
you love so much.

18:40.120 --> 18:42.286
Milhouse is not a place,
it's a nerd.

18:42.288 --> 18:43.654
Oh, well,
there you go.

18:43.656 --> 18:45.556
BART:
<i> So that's it.</i>

18:45.558 --> 18:48.993
<i> I learned playing with women's</i>
<i> hearts is a dangerous game.</i>

18:48.995 --> 18:50.895
<i> And it's wrong to take</i>
<i> advantage of the elderly.</i>

18:54.334 --> 18:55.766
And Grampa?

18:55.768 --> 18:58.970
I'm sorry I embarrassed
you on Grandparents' Day.

18:58.972 --> 19:02.240
Geez! I thought
<i>my</i> stories were long.

19:06.579 --> 19:09.747
Homer?
Uh... what?

19:09.749 --> 19:12.316
I know about the $600.

19:12.318 --> 19:13.584
You're right, Marge.

19:13.586 --> 19:14.819
We spent too much.

19:14.821 --> 19:16.087
Bart was a gigolo.

19:16.089 --> 19:17.321
What are you gonna do?

19:17.323 --> 19:18.789
Be mad at the world?

19:18.791 --> 19:20.658
(groans) Maybe you
could say something

19:20.660 --> 19:22.193
to make me feel better.

19:22.195 --> 19:23.761
The kids are fine.

19:23.763 --> 19:26.330
The game is a fad,
and in no time at all

19:26.332 --> 19:28.866
you'll be worried
about something else.

19:28.868 --> 19:31.836
Huh, I do feel better.

19:31.838 --> 19:34.939
Hmm, you know, the last
couple of pies I baked

19:34.941 --> 19:36.340
haven't been great.

19:36.342 --> 19:37.942
There you go.

19:50.723 --> 19:53.224
I like your hair. Finger-combed?

19:53.226 --> 19:55.560
Yes, because I decide
how my hair looks.

19:55.562 --> 19:57.228
MRS. SKINNER:
Seymour!

19:57.230 --> 19:59.730
Just wanted to tell you
I'm here with a real man.

19:59.732 --> 20:03.000
My silhouette's replacing
yours on the stairs.

20:03.002 --> 20:04.669
<i> (Milhouse chuckles)</i>

20:04.671 --> 20:06.704
So enjoy your meal, son.

20:06.706 --> 20:08.005
I'm buying dessert.

20:08.007 --> 20:09.507
Oh, that's so nice.

20:09.509 --> 20:10.741
For you,

20:10.743 --> 20:12.343
not that son-snatcher.

20:12.345 --> 20:13.344
(grumbles)

20:13.346 --> 20:15.479
♪ ♪

20:22.021 --> 20:25.690
LISA: ♪<i> I want to be</i>
<i> the very best</i> ♪

20:25.692 --> 20:29.260
♪<i> This is my new career</i> ♪

20:29.262 --> 20:32.029
HOMER: ♪<i> I want to give</i>
<i> this game a rest</i> ♪

20:32.031 --> 20:36.000
♪<i> I've been playing</i>
<i> since last year</i> ♪

20:36.002 --> 20:39.003
SEA CAPTAIN:
♪<i> I play it on my little boat</i> ♪

20:39.005 --> 20:40.771
♪<i> Sitting in a cove</i> ♪

20:40.773 --> 20:42.540
<i> Yar.</i>

20:42.542 --> 20:45.443
OTTO: ♪<i> I ran my bus</i>
<i> right off a cliff</i> ♪

20:45.445 --> 20:49.180
♪<i> Was playing while I drove</i> ♪

20:49.182 --> 20:50.548
LISA: ♪<i> This fad was hot</i> ♪

20:50.550 --> 20:52.250
♪<i> And then was not</i> ♪

20:52.252 --> 20:55.786
♪<i> These things come and go</i> ♪

20:55.788 --> 20:58.856
HOMER:
♪<i> All I know is once again</i> ♪

20:58.858 --> 21:00.925
♪<i> I wasted lots of dough.</i> ♪

21:01.961 --> 21:03.027
(snarling, growling)

21:03.029 --> 21:04.428
Shh!

